Known apt limitation -- googling for 'Dynamic MMap ran out of room' (ie the
error message) along with 'apt' or 'apt-get' would you have told you so. In
fact, Google Chrome even completed the sentence for me.  So do the query and
follow the first hit

http://www.google.com/search?q=Dynamic+MMap+ran+out+of+room+apt-get

FWIW newer systems don't seem to use it. I can't find this in any of my
apt.conf files -- but I have needed it in the past.

Now, if I may: Please do not use this list for generic Debian help. It is for
the R / Debian intersection only.  We value our signal to noise ratio, so
let's all make an effort at keeping it high.

Dirk

